Module mesakit.graph.core
Package com.telenav.mesakit.graph

Class Edge

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.graph.GraphElement
com.telenav.mesakit.graph.Edge
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.core.string.AsIndentedString, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.collection.Indexed, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.collection.LongKeyed, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Named, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.DoubleQuantizable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.Quantizable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.Stringable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.string.StringSource, com.telenav.kivakit.validation.Validatable, Road, LocationSequence, Bounded, Intersectable
Direct Known Subclasses:
HeavyWeightEdge, OsmEdge, WorldEdge
public abstract class Edge extends GraphElement implements Bounded, Intersectable, Road, LocationSequence
An edge in a Graph connecting two Vertexes. In the case of PBF graphs, edges are sections of ways between intersections and other features (see EdgeSectioner and WaySectioningGraphLoader for details on how PBF ways are sectioned by the PBF loader).

An Edge is "flyweight" object, having only three fields: a Graph reference, an EdgeIdentifier and an index value that is used to efficiently retrieve EdgeAttributes from an EdgeStore. This design makes edges very cheap to construct, allowing a truly object-oriented style of programming.

The Edge class is central to the Graph API and has a large number of methods. While this can seem overwhelming, the functionality breaks down into categories that are easier to digest:

Categories of Functionality

  • Graph - Find edges in a graph
  • Identity - Edge identifiers
  • Attributes - Discover edge attributes and properties
  • Edges - Find related edges
  • Routes - Construct routes from edges
  • Vertexes, Nodes and ShapePoints - Edge end-points and the nodes in-between
  • Metrics - Edge measurements
  • Geometry - The shape of edges
  • Spatial Search - Locate edges with spatial searches
  • Metadata - Metadata associated with all edges
  • Tags - Key / value pairs associated with edges
  • Road Classification - Determine the type of an edge
  • Road PropertyMap - Attributes of the road that an edge belongs to
  • Turns - Information regarding different types of turns between edges
  • Traffic - Traffic information identifiers for an edge
  • Region and Locale - Administrative areas and locale information
  • Speed and Travel Time - Historical and free-flow travel information
  • Testing and Debugging - Methods helpful in testing and debugging
  • OSM-Specific - Methods that are specific to the OsmDataSpecification (for convenience)

A few methods that have internal uses have been omitted. Some methods also show up under more than one category to make it easier to find functionality.

Graph

  • GraphElement.graph() - The Graph that this edge belongs to
  • Graph.edgeCount() - The number of edges in a graph
  • Graph.edgeNearest(Location) - The edge nearest to the given location
  • Graph.edgeNearest(Location, Distance) - The edge nearest to the given location, within the given maximum distance
  • Graph.edgeNearest(Location, Distance, TransportMode) - The edge navigable in the given Edge.TransportMode that is nearest to the given location, within the given maximum distance
  • Graph.edgeForIdentifier(EdgeIdentifier) - The edge for the given identifier
  • Graph.edgeForIdentifier(long) - The edge for the given identifier
  • Graph.edgeForIdentifier(MapEdgeIdentifier) - The edge corresponding to the given MapEdgeIdentifier of the form "[way-identifier]:[from-node-identifier]:[to-node-identifier]"
  • Graph.edges() - The sequence of all edges in a graph
  • Graph.edgesIntersecting(Rectangle) - The sequence of all edges in the graph that intersect (by definition of Intersectable.intersects(Rectangle)) the given rectangle

Identity

  • identifier() - The EdgeIdentifier for this edge
  • GraphElement.identifierAsLong() - The edge identifier as a long rather than as an object
  • wayIdentifier() - The PbfWayIdentifier for the way that this edge came from
  • mapEdgeIdentifier() - An identifier for the edge in terms of MapIdentifiers taking the form "[way-identifier]:[from-node-identifier]:[to-node-identifier]"
  • directionalWayIdentifier() - The PbfWayIdentifier for this edge, but negative if the edge is reversed

Attributes

  • attributes() - The EdgeAttributes this edge supports according to its DataSpecification
  • GraphElement.supports(Attribute) - True if this edge supports the given Attribute
  • differencesFrom(Edge) - Determines the differences between the attributes of this edge and the given edge
  • properties() - A list of each display GraphElementProperty this edge supports according to its DataSpecification

Edges

  • relations() - The set of relations that reference this edge
  • forward() - The forward edge for this edge, having a non-negative identifier
  • isForward() - True if this is a forward edge with a positive identifier
  • isForwardOrReverseOf(Edge) - True if this is the forward or reverse edge of the given edge
  • reverse() - The reverse edge corresponding to this edge (whether forward or not) and having a non-negative identifier
  • reversed() - This edge, reversed, if it is a two-way road. A forward edge becomes a reverse edge and a reverse edge a forward edge.
  • isReverse() - True if this is a reverse edge (on a two-way road) with a negative identifier
  • next() - The edge that this edge leads to. If there is more than one, an arbitrary next edge is returned
  • previous() - The edge that this edge comes from. If there is more than one, an arbitrary previous edge is returned
  • toEdgesWithoutThisEdge() - Set of ALL edges connected to the "to" vertex of this edge, but not including this edge or its reverse
  • fromEdgesWithoutThisEdge() - Set of ALL edges connected to the "from" vertex of this edge, but not including this edge or its reverse
  • inEdgeSequence() - Decoded of edges inbound to the "from" vertex of this edge
  • inEdges() - Set of edges inbound to the "from" vertex of this edge
  • inEdgesWithoutReversed() - Set of edges inbound to the "from" vertex of this edge, not including the reverse of this edge if it is two-way
  • outEdgeSequence() - Decoded of edges outbound to the "to" vertex of this edge
  • outEdges() - Set of edges outbound to the "to" vertex of this edge
  • outEdgesWithoutReversed() - Set of edges outbound to the "to" vertex of this edge, not including the reverse of this edge if it is two-way
  • nearbyEdges(Distance, Matcher) ()} - Edges within the given distance of this edge that match the given matcher
  • leadsTo(Edge) - True if this edge leads to the given edge
  • isConnectedTo(Edge) - True if this edge is connected to the given edge
  • isConnectedTo(Vertex) - True if this edge is connected to the given vertex
  • connectedEdges() - The set of all edges connected to this edge, not including this edge
  • connectedEdgesWithoutReversed() - The set of all edges connected to this edge, not including this edge or its reverse if it is a two-way road
  • otherEdges(Vertex) - All the edges other than this one that are connected to this edge at the given vertex
  • mapWay() - This edge as a way in the map data

Routes

  • intersecting(Rectangle) - A matcher for edges that intersect the given bounds
  • within(Rectangle) - A matcher for edges within the given bounds
  • asRoute() - This edge as a one-edge route
  • route(Navigator, Maximum) - The route from this edge discovered by the given Navigator up to the given maximum number of edges
  • route(Navigator, Distance) - The route from this edge discovered by the given Navigator up to the given maximum length
  • route(Navigator, RouteLimiter) - The route from this edge discovered by the given Navigator, restricted by the given RouteLimiter
  • route(Matcher) - The route from this edge of edges matching the given matcher
  • leadsTo(Route) - True if this edge leads to the given route
  • inRoute(Navigator, RouteLimiter) - An inbound route as discovered by a navigator within the limits of the route limiter
  • outRoute(Navigator, RouteLimiter) - An outbound route as discovered by a navigator within the limits of the route limiter
  • nonBranchingRoute(Maximum) - A route from this edge with no more than the given number of edges, which does not branch
  • nonBranchingRouteWithSameName(Maximum) - A non-branching route from this edge limited to edges with the same base road name
  • wayAsRoute() - The way that this edge belongs to as a route
  • vertexConnecting(Edge) - The vertex that connects this edge to the given edge, or null if none exists

Vertexes, Nodes and ShapePoints

  • from() -The "from" vertex of the edge
  • to() - The "to" vertex of the edge
  • fromLocation() - The location of the "from" vertex of the edge
  • toLocation() - The location of the "to" vertex of the edge
  • fromNodeIdentifier() - The MapNodeIdentifier of the "from" end of the edge
  • toNodeIdentifier() - The MapNodeIdentifier of the "to" end of the edge
  • fromVertexIdentifier() - The VertexIdentifier of the "from" end of the edge
  • toVertexIdentifier() - The VertexIdentifier of the "to" end of the edge
  • locationSequence() - The locations from the beginning of this edges road shape Polyline to the end
  • oppositeVertex(Vertex) - The opposite vertex to the given vertex on this edge
  • shapePoints() - The edge's shape points, if it #supportsFullPbfNodeInformation
  • shapePointsWithoutVertexes() - The edge's shape points without vertexes, if it #supportsFullPbfNodeInformation
  • shapePointNodeIdentifiers() - The edge's node identifiers, if it #supportsFullPbfNodeInformation
  • supportsNodeIdentifiers() - True if the edge is in a graph supporting full node information. This is very space inefficient and is generally only used by tools to improve the map, like the map enhancer (Cygnus)

Metrics

  • bounds() - The bounding area of the edge, based on its road shape, not its endpoints
  • distanceTo(Edge) - The shortest distance to the given edge
  • length() - The length of this edge along its road shape Polyline
  • lengthInMillimeters() - The edge length in millimeters
  • turnAngleTo(Edge, Chirality) - The turn angle from this edge to the given edge using the given Angle.Chirality

Geometry

  • asSegment() - This edge as a segment from the "from" vertex to the "to" vertex, ignoring any road shape
  • finalHeading() - The heading of the last segment of this edge's road shape
  • initialHeading() - The heading of the first segment of this edge's road shape
  • heading() - Same as finalHeading()
  • roadShape() - The shape of this edge as a Polyline
  • isShaped() - True if this edge has a polyline road shape
  • isSegment() - True if this edge is just a single segment and does not have a polyline road shape
  • turnAngleTo(Edge, Chirality) - The turn angle from this edge to the given edge using the given Angle.Chirality
  • rightTurnAngleTo(Edge) - The clockwise (right) turn angle from this edge to the given edge
  • leftTurnAngleTo(Edge) - The counter-clockwise (left) angle from this edge to the given edge
  • straightOnTurnAngleTo(Edge) - The smallest turn angle from this edge to the given edge
  • firstSegment() - The first segment in this edge's road shape
  • lastSegment() - The last segment in this edge's road shape
  • intersects(Rectangle) - True if this edge's road shape intersects the given rectangle
  • endNearestTo(Located) - The end of this edge nearest to the given location
  • isParallelTo(Edge) - True if this edge is parallel to the given edge
  • isPerpendicularTo(Edge) - True if this edge is perpendicular to the given edge
  • crosses(Edge) - True if this edge crosses the given edge

Spatial Search

  • Graph.edgesIntersecting(Rectangle) - The sequence of all edges in the graph that intersect (by definition of Intersectable.intersects(Rectangle)) the given rectangle
  • Graph.edgeNearest(Location) - The edge nearest to the given location
  • Graph.edgeNearest(Location, Distance) - The edge nearest to the given location, within the given maximum distance
  • Graph.edgeNearest(Location, Distance, TransportMode) - The edge navigable in the given Edge.TransportMode that is nearest to the given location, within the given maximum distance
  • intersects(Rectangle) - True if this edge's road shape intersects the given rectangle
  • endNearestTo(Located) - The end of this edge nearest to the given location
  • isInside(Rectangle) - True if this edge is inside the given rectangle

Metadata

  • GraphElement.metadata() - The Metadata of the Graph that this edge belongs to
  • GraphElement.dataSpecification() - The DataSpecification for this edge
  • GraphElement.lastModificationTime() - The last time the way that this edge belongs to was changed
  • GraphElement.pbfUserName() - The user who most recently changed this edge's way
  • GraphElement.pbfUserIdentifier() - The identifier of the user who most recently changed this edge's way
  • GraphElement.pbfChangeSetIdentifier() - The most recent change set identifier of the way that this edge belongs to
  • GraphElement.pbfRevisionNumber() - The current revision number of the way that this edge belongs to

Tags

  • GraphElement.hasTag(String) - True if this edge has a tag with the given key
  • GraphElement.tag(String) - The Tag for the given key
  • GraphElement.tagMap() - A PbfTagMap of the tags that belong to this edge
  • GraphElement.tagList() - A PbfTagList of the tags that belong to this edge
  • GraphElement.tagValue(String) - The value of any tag with the given key or null if there is no such tag

Road Classification

  • isLink() - True if this edge is a link
  • isIntersectionEdge() - True if this edge is in an intersection
  • isJunctionEdge() - True if this edge is junction edge in an intersection
  • isConnector() - True if this edge connects roadways
  • leadsToDeadEnd() - True if this edge does not lead anywhere (except turning around)
  • isJoiningEdge() - True if this edge merges with another edge
  • isClipped() - True if this edge was clean-cut as part of a WorldGraph
  • isMainRoad() - True if this edge is considered a main road
  • isNavigable(TransportMode) - True if this edge is navigable in the given transport mode: car, foot, bike
  • isOffRamp() - True if this edge is a freeway off ramp
  • isOnRamp() - True if this edge is a freeway on ramp
  • isLink() - True if this edge is a link from one road to another
  • isDrivable() - True if this edge supports Edge.TransportMode.DRIVE
  • isSoftCut() - True if this edge was soft-cut
  • isUnderConstruction() - True if this edge is under construction
  • isTwoWay() - True if this edge has a reverse edge
  • isTollRoad() - True if this edge is part of a toll road
  • leadsToFork() - True if the "to" vertex of this edge forks to two or more edges
  • isLoop() - True if this edge connects back to itself in a loop
  • isRoundabout() - True if this edge is part of a roundabout
  • isOneWay() - True if this edge has no reverse edge
  • isRamp() - True if this edge is part of a freeway ramp
  • isClosedToThroughTraffic() - True if this edge is closed
  • entersRoundabout() - True if this edge enters a roundabout
  • isNormal() - True if this edge has RoadType#NORMAL
  • isRoutingShortCut() - True if this edge has RoadType#ROUTING_SHORTCUT

Road PropertyMap

  • hasRoadName() - True if this edge has at least one name
  • isNamed() - True if this road has a name
  • isNameless() - True if this road has no name
  • roadName() - The most important name of this road
  • roadName(RoadName.Type) - The name for this road of the given type
  • roadNames() - All the names of this road
  • roadNames(RoadName.Type) - All the names of the given type for this road
  • hasSameRoadNameAs(Edge) - True if this edge has the same road name as the given edge
  • isOnSameRoadWithSameTypeAs(Edge) - True if this edge has the same road name as the given edge and has the same road type and sub-type
  • isOnSameRoadAs(Edge) - True if this edge is on the same road as the given edge, as determined by the road names
  • safeRoadName() - A name for this edge that is never null
  • displayRoadName() - A name for this edge that is suitable for display to an end-user
  • hasSameStandardizedBaseNameAs(Edge) - True if this edge has the same base name as the given edge
  • roadFunctionalClass() - The RoadFunctionalClass of this edge
  • isSameFunctionalClassAs(Edge) - True if this edge has the same functional class as the given edge
  • isMoreImportantThan(Edge) - True if this edge has a higher functional class than the given edge. If the classes are the same, the road type is used to break the tie
  • roadShape() - The Polyline shape of this edge
  • roadState() - The state of this edge: one-way, two-way or closed
  • roadType() - The type of this edge: freeway, highway, local road, etc.
  • roadSubType() - The sub-type of this edge: main road, intersection link, ramp, roundabout, etc.
  • roadSurface() - The surface of this edge: paved, unpaved or poor condition
  • laneCount() - The number of lanes on this edge
  • hovLaneCount() - The number of HOV lanes on this edge
  • isShaped() - True if this edge has a road shape with more than one segment
  • bridgeType() - The type of bridge for this edge: none, tunnel, overpass or underpass
  • isOnSameWay(Edge) - True if this edge part of the same way as the given edge
  • signPostSupport() - The support for sign posts on this edge

Turns

  • turnAngleTo(Edge, Chirality)
  • turnRestrictions()
  • turnType(Edge)
  • turnType(Edge, TwoHeadingTurnClassifier)
  • hardestRight(Angle) - The hardest right-turn edge from this edge within the given tolerance
  • hardestLeft(Angle) - The hardest left-turn edge from this edge within the given tolerance
  • mostStraightOn(Angle) - The most straight-on edge from this edge within the given tolerance
  • rightTurnAngleTo(Edge) - The right-turn angle from the last segment of this edge to the first segment of the given edge
  • leftTurnAngleTo(Edge) - The left-turn angle from the last segment of this edge to the first segment of the given edge
  • straightOnTurnAngleTo(Edge) - The smallest angle from the last segment of this edge to the first segment of the given edge

Speed and Travel Time

  • speedLimit() - The speed limit on this edge
  • freeFlowSpeed() - The speed of normal traffic flow on this edge
  • freeFlowForFunctionalClass() - Typical speed of traffic on edges of this functional class
  • travelTime() - The amount of time required to travel this edge at free flow speed
  • travelTime(Speed) - The time required to travel this edge at the given speed
  • travelTimeForFunctionalClass() - The time required to travel this edge based on the typical speed on this edge's functional class
  • travelTimeInMilliseconds() - The travel time for this edge at free flow speed in milliseconds

Region and Locale

  • continent() - The continent where this edge exists
  • country() - The country that owns this edge
  • state() - The state where this edge exists
  • metropolitanArea() - The most important metropolitan area that owns this edge
  • locale() - The MapLocale for this edge (which is distinct from java.util.Locale

Testing and Debugging

  • asHeavyWeight() - This edge as a HeavyWeightEdge
  • GraphElement.isHeavyWeight() - True if this edge is a HeavyWeightEdge
  • populateWithTestValues() - Populates this HeavyWeightEdge with test values
  • AsIndentedString.asString() - A string representation of the EdgeProperties of this edge accessible through Stringable.asString()

OSM-Specific

  • GraphElement.isOsm() - True if this is an OSM edge
  • osmIsLink() - True if this edge is an OSM link
  • osmIsOneWay() - True if this edge has been labeled as an OSM one-way
  • osmIsRoundabout() - True if this edge is on a roundabout based on OSM tags
  • osmIsServiceWay() - True if this edge is an OSM service way
  • osmIsExitToTagged() - True if this edge is tagged with OSM exit-to
  • osmIsDestinationTagged() - True this edge has an OSM destination tag
  • osmIsMotorwayJunctionReferenceTagged() - True this edge has an OSM junction reference tag
  • osmIsDoubleDigitized() - True this edge has been detected in OSM as being double-digitized.
  • osmMaximumDoubleDigitizationSeparation() - The maximum separation of detected OSM double-digitized ways
  • fromGradeSeparation() - The GradeSeparation for the "from" end of this edge
  • toGradeSeparation() - The GradeSeparation for the "to" end of this edge
  • osmCouldBeDoubleDigitized() - True if this edge could be detected as OSM double-digitized
